36:30.800 --> 36:35.283
The squeaky wheel gets the grease,
and the cactus never gets water?

36:35.640 --> 36:37.210
Come here. Come here.
Come here. Come here.

36:37.280 --> 36:41.808
You need to start thinking of yourself
as indispensable.

36:41.960 --> 36:45.123
Okay, first of all, I'm not.
I'm totally dispensable.

36:45.200 --> 36:47.771
I mean, on a practical level,
you'd be fine without me.

36:47.840 --> 36:50.047
Do you realize
that Paul faked the ankle thing today

36:50.120 --> 36:51.565
because he wanted you
to come pick him up at school

36:51.640 --> 36:52.641
and then you didn't even show?

36:52.800 --> 36:54.040
What do you mean?

36:54.240 --> 36:57.961
He ran on it when I asked him
to go check on Justine. He forgot.

36:58.960 --> 37:01.088
- Well, that's weird.
- No, it's not weird.

37:01.160 --> 37:04.050
You want to know why?
Because his mother is in Reykjavik right now

37:04.120 --> 37:07.044
studying the maternal techniques
of the Icelandic.

37:07.840 --> 37:09.968
He needs his father's attention.

37:12.040 --> 37:13.451
So do I.

37:16.040 --> 37:19.726
Let's go away together, just us.
As soon as Georgette gets back.

37:22.160 --> 37:23.161
Please?

37:24.840 --> 37:26.808
I'm gonna start pouting more.

37:27.120 --> 37:29.487
Georgette'll give you a tutorial.
She's good at that.

37:37.400 --> 37:39.687
Who did you sit with at snack?

37:40.600 --> 37:42.602
- Allison.
- Maggie?

37:43.800 --> 37:46.087
Hi! Hi, Guy!

37:46.200 --> 37:48.646
Hi. This is my friend Guy.

37:49.920 --> 37:50.967
Is that...

37:52.040 --> 37:54.407
No! No! This is Lily. I got married.

37:54.840 --> 37:56.444
I should have told you.

37:56.520 --> 38:00.525
I met my husband around the same time
that you gave me the sample.

38:05.120 --> 38:08.283
- How are you?
- Intense. Intense.

38:08.560 --> 38:12.804
I just heard that Whole Foods are gonna be
carrying my pickles nationally, so...

38:12.880 --> 38:15.565
Yeah, we'll have to expand production
post haste!

38:15.640 --> 38:16.641
That's amazing.

38:16.720 --> 38:18.643
So I'm just manning the stall.

38:18.720 --> 38:21.485
Get away from the chaos at the factory.

38:21.560 --> 38:24.609
Well... Do you still have
those Bavarian pickles?

38:24.680 --> 38:28.002
Sure do. They're our most popular pickle.

38:28.080 --> 38:31.482
- Well, let's get a... Can I buy a jar?
- Yes!

38:31.560 --> 38:33.688
When are we gonna eat the pickles?

38:33.760 --> 38:35.762
Let's go get some pickles.
Let's see what they are.

38:35.840 --> 38:38.525
Sounds good. Oh, my goodness.

38:38.640 --> 38:41.689
That's the biggest jar of pickles
I've ever seen.

38:41.760 --> 38:43.569
How much do I owe you?

38:43.720 --> 38:46.405
- It's a wedding present.
- Thank you.

38:47.200 --> 38:50.090
- Bye! Okay, let's go.
- Bye, Lily!

38:50.160 --> 38:51.889
We're gonna take our pickle baby home.

38:52.760 --> 38:55.001
I am so glad you're you.

38:55.080 --> 38:58.163
I am so glad you're you, wiglet. Bye!

38:58.760 --> 38:59.841
Bye.

39:06.760 --> 39:07.761
Still warm.

39:09.880 --> 39:11.723
Hey, Georgette canceled her trip.

39:11.800 --> 39:15.122
So she's gonna want the kids next week
after all.

39:22.280 --> 39:24.123
I'm Mrs. Jeffries, aren't I?

39:24.720 --> 39:29.248
I'm the colorless, efficient postal worker
that you fall in love with

39:29.320 --> 39:32.210
because she makes your life so much easier.

39:32.280 --> 39:35.887
I came up with Mrs. Jeffries
before we even met.

39:35.960 --> 39:39.487
Yeah, well, you've turned me
into her, then.

39:41.320 --> 39:43.288
At least I don't have a mustache.

39:45.120 --> 39:46.121
Yet.

39:50.560 --> 39:52.767
Do you want to hear your horoscope?

39:53.920 --> 39:54.967
No.

39:59.280 --> 40:01.169
I'm terrified that I'm falling
out of love with him.

40:01.240 --> 40:03.607
Like, really out of love.

40:03.880 --> 40:06.406
Felicia and I fall in and out of love
pretty much every week.

40:06.480 --> 40:08.050
You can't be so idealistic.

40:08.120 --> 40:12.569
I wanted to help him become a fiction writer,
and now all he does is write,

40:12.680 --> 40:16.651
and the novel is 500 pages long
and I don't even think it's half done.

40:16.720 --> 40:19.166
- Have you read the whole thing?
- Most of it.

40:19.240 --> 40:20.366
You still like it?

40:21.520 --> 40:23.966
- It's gotten more and more complicated.
- Yeah.

40:24.040 --> 40:28.443
Do you think it's possible to be too smart
to be a novelist?

40:28.520 --> 40:30.443
I haven't heard that one.

40:30.520 --> 40:31.601
Do you think
there's something wrong with me?

40:31.680 --> 40:32.681
Wrong with you?

40:32.760 --> 40:36.685
Yeah, that I have a condition
where I always fall out of love.

40:38.080 --> 40:39.445
Maybe.

40:39.520 --> 40:41.010
Shut up!

40:41.080 --> 40:43.447
- What? Yes! No!
- Really? You think I have a condition?

40:43.520 --> 40:45.249
No! Yes! I don't know! I don't know.

40:45.320 --> 40:47.926
Maybe! No, no, you don't. You know what?

40:48.040 --> 40:51.203
Maybe you just haven't met the right guy yet.
Ask Felicia. Don't ask me.

40:51.280 --> 40:52.805
I'm not the right guy.

40:53.160 --> 40:55.083
Does he ever walk?

40:55.160 --> 40:58.801
Max? He's gotta finish that book by Friday.

40:58.880 --> 41:01.884
Does he ever walk? Yes.
He's the captain of the soccer team.

41:01.960 --> 41:05.203
- What is it? Stroller soccer?
- You're hilarious.

41:09.520 --> 41:10.851
I will be honest with you.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.731
This book was born from pain.

41:14.800 --> 41:19.886
My husband, whom I am not ashamed to say
I loved with all my heart,

41:20.160 --> 41:22.083
though we had a difficult relationship,

41:23.520 --> 41:27.764
had an affair with a younger woman,
left me and started a new family.

41:28.960 --> 41:31.884
And what I gleaned
from this exquisite torture

41:31.960 --> 41:35.407
are the thoughts
which this act of betrayal to me as a woman

41:35.480 --> 41:38.131
provoked in me as an anthropologist.

41:38.200 --> 41:39.725
I must ask myself,

41:39.800 --> 41:44.044
is the contemporary obsession
with exclusive possession

41:44.120 --> 41:47.602
ruining our chances of marital happiness?

41:48.000 --> 41:49.570
Excuse me.

41:49.640 --> 41:50.926
Maggie?

41:51.760 --> 41:53.091
Yes! Hi.

41:53.280 --> 41:56.090
I recognized you
from a picture on Justine's phone.

41:59.440 --> 42:04.241
I wanted to... I wanted to see your reading.
It was really...

42:06.360 --> 42:09.762
I want to say thank you for taking such
good care of the children while I was gone.

42:09.880 --> 42:12.360
I know it's been a burden. I appreciate it.

42:12.600 --> 42:15.046
You're welcome. They're wonderful kids.

42:15.760 --> 42:17.808
We should get together sometime.

42:19.400 --> 42:22.802
I feel I've been rather
childish about all this.

42:23.560 --> 42:28.168
We have to face the fact that we are
raising them together, the three of us, yeah.

42:29.960 --> 42:31.405
I would love that.

42:32.520 --> 42:34.124
Call me some time.

42:34.200 --> 42:35.804
It's easy to get my number.

42:41.960 --> 42:45.567
- You bought a book?
- I couldn't resist.

42:45.640 --> 42:49.440
- Do we need to get it signed?
- I think we do.

42:52.200 --> 42:54.521
- Georgette is fascinating.
- Really?

42:54.600 --> 42:59.527
Yes. She's warm and powerful

42:59.600 --> 43:05.164
and charming all at once and
I can see why he was so obsessed with her.

43:05.240 --> 43:08.005
I don't think "easy to live with"
was on that list, though, you know.

43:09.520 --> 43:10.681
I like her.

43:11.320 --> 43:14.802
I actually like her! I'm such a blockhead.

43:15.160 --> 43:19.210
I thought I was rescuing John
from this monstrous egomaniac,

43:19.280 --> 43:21.009
so he could finally finish his book.

43:21.080 --> 43:24.926
I thought I knew better how to run his life,
that I was gonna fix everything.

43:25.000 --> 43:26.889
And he's totally self-absorbed,

43:27.000 --> 43:31.289
while I do every single practical thing
and make the money, and on top of that...

43:32.160 --> 43:35.846
If it weren't for Lily,
I would say I made a terrible mistake.

43:37.400 --> 43:40.802
It's too bad you can't give him back
to his ex-wife. Right?

43:49.320 --> 43:50.560
I hate brussel sprouts.

43:50.640 --> 43:52.051
They're a little hard.

44:26.480 --> 44:29.006
So now it suits the captors
to have the little prisoners moved.

44:29.080 --> 44:30.764
Aren't you excited to see Mama?

44:33.160 --> 44:35.128
Of course, I'm excited to see Mama.

44:35.200 --> 44:37.931
I'm just sick of never knowing
where any of my stuff is.

44:38.000 --> 44:41.527
I can't wait until I have kids
so I can push them around.

44:44.400 --> 44:47.165
Sometimes I wonder
if she is a little dim-witted.

44:47.240 --> 44:48.651
What is she doing?

44:48.720 --> 44:49.721
She's nice.

44:50.600 --> 44:53.524
You're like a dog.
You love whoever feeds you.

44:53.600 --> 44:54.442
Not true.

44:54.520 --> 44:56.443
I'm sorry. Is there a problem here?

44:57.280 --> 44:59.009
No. I just can't believe

44:59.080 --> 45:01.845
that I found a legal parking spot
right in front of your mom's house.

45:01.920 --> 45:04.924
- You're coming inside?
- Just to say hi.

45:05.160 --> 45:06.286
Okay.

45:10.800 --> 45:12.131
- Hi.
- Hi.

45:12.840 --> 45:13.841
Hi!

45:15.280 --> 45:16.645
Hello, Maggie.

45:16.720 --> 45:19.564
Hi. John had a meeting,
so he asked me to drop them off.

45:19.640 --> 45:21.369
- Come in.
- Thanks.

45:22.280 --> 45:25.523
Now, I have made you a nice snack.

45:25.680 --> 45:27.125
And you are allowed to watch

45:27.200 --> 45:30.170
one single episode of something ghastly
while eating it.

45:30.240 --> 45:31.969
The snacks are already in the den.

45:32.080 --> 45:34.242
- And no fighting about what it is, Paul.
- Okay.

45:37.440 --> 45:41.809
- I was about to make some coffee? Or tea?
- Coffee would be great.

45:42.160 --> 45:43.969
Your place is really nice.

45:44.480 --> 45:46.005
Columbia housing.

45:46.760 --> 45:48.683
I put butter in mine.

45:48.760 --> 45:52.128
- Nullifies the afternoon sugar cravings.
- Great.

46:19.960 --> 46:22.201
- Lovely photo.
- Yes.

46:24.480 --> 46:25.481
Thank you.

46:34.520 --> 46:36.363
It's so good to finally meet you.

46:36.480 --> 46:38.801
I won't pretend
it doesn't cost me something.

46:38.880 --> 46:39.961
Of course.

46:40.040 --> 46:42.202
- I'm not into fakery.
- Me neither.

46:42.480 --> 46:46.451
I detest the role of the spurned wife.
I won't play it.

46:46.520 --> 46:48.522
- You're not.
- Am I not?

46:48.760 --> 46:54.483
No. You still have
such a deep connection to John.

46:54.560 --> 46:57.723
We have managed
to remain friends, it's true.

46:58.520 --> 47:02.445
- Well, and your phone calls.
- Do you disapprove of them?

47:02.520 --> 47:03.646
No.

47:03.720 --> 47:07.406
The marriage has dissolved,
but we are still parenting together.

47:08.560 --> 47:13.248
Well, I mean, it's not just parenting.

47:13.320 --> 47:16.847
You guys are on the phone,
like, several times a day.

47:16.920 --> 47:19.002
Don't get me wrong. I think it's great.

47:19.080 --> 47:20.923
So I...

47:23.360 --> 47:24.600
It's just...

47:26.600 --> 47:27.840
Yes?

47:29.240 --> 47:31.766
Well, it's obvious
that you're still in love with him.

47:32.400 --> 47:34.129
What the hell are you playing at?

47:34.640 --> 47:36.608
John and I are in trouble.

47:36.680 --> 47:39.251
And I don't think he realizes
how much trouble we're in,

47:39.320 --> 47:41.084
or he doesn't want to know.

47:41.160 --> 47:43.811
And then, when I saw you at the reading,

47:43.920 --> 47:47.527
I realized that
there might be an opportunity,

47:47.600 --> 47:49.921
an opening to somehow

47:51.720 --> 47:54.246
get the two of you back together.

47:54.320 --> 47:56.402
I see. I see.

47:57.080 --> 48:00.687
So you are tired of your little affair?

48:00.760 --> 48:02.285
You're all done with it.

48:02.400 --> 48:05.131
Now you want to make sure
you don't feel guilty

48:05.200 --> 48:09.569
so you're going to manipulate us all
into some absurd happy ending.

48:09.640 --> 48:11.802
I have met a lot
of control freaks in my life,

48:11.880 --> 48:17.011
in fact, I thought I was one, but you,
you make me look like an amateur.

48:17.120 --> 48:18.565
I didn't mean to insult you.

48:18.640 --> 48:20.529
Have the decency to leave him

48:20.600 --> 48:24.400
and face the fact that you poisoned my life
and my children's life,

48:24.480 --> 48:27.006
and probably John's life
with your own selfishness.

48:27.080 --> 48:29.048
That's your burden. You earned it.

48:29.640 --> 48:30.766
Wait a minute.

48:30.840 --> 48:34.925
If you had such a perfect marriage,
why was John miserable?

48:35.000 --> 48:37.890
You neglected him and you used him
and you didn't believe in his talent.

48:37.960 --> 48:39.121
If I am so awful,

48:39.200 --> 48:41.009
why are you trying to get me back together
with him?

48:41.080 --> 48:42.684
Because I think that, actually,

48:42.760 --> 48:46.765
even though I do think you are
pretty self-absorbed and extremely needy,

48:46.840 --> 48:49.286
that he needs it. It keeps him in balance.

48:49.360 --> 48:52.523
It's thinking about you that stops him
from only thinking about himself.

48:52.840 --> 48:54.171
Leave. Leave. Leave.

48:54.240 --> 48:55.924
- Leave? You want me to leave.
- Leave my house, leave.

48:56.000 --> 48:57.570
- Okay, I'm leaving. Okay, sorry.
- Leave, leave.

49:07.600 --> 49:10.206
I've never been so humiliated in my life.

49:11.320 --> 49:13.084
I am in such deep oatmeal.

49:13.880 --> 49:15.120
What was I thinking?

49:15.200 --> 49:18.682
- Maybe you're having a psychotic episode.
- But it was such a good idea.

49:18.760 --> 49:20.888
You know, life doesn't work this way,
you dufus.

49:20.960 --> 49:23.850
You can't take everything
and stuff it back in the box.

49:24.880 --> 49:26.405
God, I think you need some help.

49:26.480 --> 49:29.643
- Why are you being so hostile?
- Because it pisses me off!

49:29.720 --> 49:32.485
- The whole thing pisses me off.
- Why?

49:32.560 --> 49:35.689
Why can't you just leave your husband
like any normal human being?

49:35.760 --> 49:37.762
- Because it would be such a waste.
- A waste!

49:37.840 --> 49:41.811
You are such a hall monitor. It's not
a waste. He's not a paper product.

49:41.880 --> 49:47.011
Love is messy. It's illogical,
it's wasteful and it's messy.

49:47.080 --> 49:50.687
And it leaves these loose threads
that go out all over the place.

49:50.800 --> 49:55.328
But you, you like things nice and neat
and tidy and ethical.

49:55.400 --> 49:58.006
But you screwed that up
the minute you got with a married man.

49:58.320 --> 50:00.368
You're not being my friend right now.

50:00.440 --> 50:02.522
Yes, I am. I am being your friend.
This is being your friend.

50:02.600 --> 50:03.601
I'm being honest with you.

50:04.360 --> 50:06.727
Good intentions.
You're all about good intentions.

50:07.040 --> 50:09.202
Little Miss Quaker Two Shoes
is gonna do the right thing.

50:09.280 --> 50:12.363
But you always somehow screw it up.

50:12.600 --> 50:14.921
- Screw you.
- Yeah, screw me. Fine.

50:16.560 --> 50:18.927
Just being honest. Trying to be a friend.

50:19.440 --> 50:22.967
Don't come over here and...
How do crayons...

50:29.000 --> 50:32.641
Hey, Maggie. Hey, I'm sorry.
Hey, hey, Maggie.

50:34.200 --> 50:37.522
Hey, I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Okay?

50:38.400 --> 50:42.325
I mean, what about Lily, huh?

50:42.400 --> 50:44.129
Fathers are a good thing, too.

50:44.560 --> 50:47.643
I know that. I know that,

50:47.720 --> 50:52.965
but I'm just as afraid of her growing up
inside of a dead marriage

50:53.040 --> 50:56.283
as her growing up
in a house without her dad.

50:58.480 --> 51:01.290
Kids can tell when people are pretending.

51:03.160 --> 51:05.083
I don't know. It's a tough one.

51:07.520 --> 51:08.851
I'm sorry.

51:12.480 --> 51:14.608
- Okay.
- Okay.

51:15.680 --> 51:18.081
Okay, okay, okay.

51:19.160 --> 51:20.161
Okay.

51:38.560 --> 51:41.643
- Yes, please.
- Yes please, what?

51:42.200 --> 51:44.851
Yes, please, I'd like to do something.

51:45.600 --> 51:48.843
Just us. If the offer's still good.

51:50.560 --> 51:52.369
Do you have anything in mind?

51:53.080 --> 51:56.687
I don't know. Maybe a local adventure.

52:04.320 --> 52:07.164
Hi. My name is Johnny Harding.

52:07.240 --> 52:09.607
And I was hoping to talk to Wang.
Is he downstairs?

52:17.320 --> 52:18.321
Stay there.

52:20.440 --> 52:24.161
Hey, hey! Johnny Harding. Yeah, thanks.
Come on.

52:38.000 --> 52:40.526
My dad used to take me
to the owner's old place.

52:48.720 --> 52:49.721
Sorry.

52:56.360 --> 52:57.566
What's in that?

52:57.640 --> 52:59.369
Just drink it, okay?

52:59.440 --> 53:01.124
This is for all the marbles.

53:02.280 --> 53:04.647
We won! We won!

53:07.920 --> 53:09.365
I should get you a pipe.

53:10.120 --> 53:12.122
Act like you know what you're doing.

53:16.080 --> 53:18.162
- Is it good?
- Yes.

53:18.240 --> 53:20.129
- Right?
- No.

53:20.200 --> 53:23.761
No! Please, no! Where did they go?

53:24.560 --> 53:26.403
Drown my sorrows.

53:26.480 --> 53:27.970
Slow down on that.

53:28.320 --> 53:29.321
And before... Thank you.

53:31.520 --> 53:33.045
Do you have a room for tonight?

53:33.960 --> 53:35.564
Is this a hotel?

53:35.640 --> 53:38.246
It is a hotel if you know it's a hotel.

53:40.600 --> 53:42.807
Thank you. What do I owe you?

53:42.880 --> 53:44.803
$50. I got $50.

53:49.360 --> 53:51.044
God! My God!

53:55.640 --> 53:57.404
Take off your clothes!

53:57.480 --> 54:00.051
- Five!
- Four!

54:00.120 --> 54:01.121
- Three!
- Three.

54:01.680 --> 54:03.967
- Two. One.
- Two. One.

54:15.600 --> 54:18.604
Take off your fucking tights!

54:42.800 --> 54:45.087
Would you ever want another baby?

54:45.160 --> 54:46.969
I'm just trying to finish this book.

54:47.040 --> 54:49.327
I think I'm gonna have to
knuckle down, you know.

54:49.400 --> 54:51.721
I mean, four kids would be a lot.

54:58.200 --> 54:59.326
What?

55:00.200 --> 55:03.807
I mean, you wouldn't even notice.
It's just one more kid for you to ignore.

55:06.240 --> 55:08.527
What kind of thing is that to say?

55:08.600 --> 55:11.729
It's a true thing. John.

55:13.280 --> 55:16.648
I mean, I support you
while you write this book.

55:16.720 --> 55:18.802
I get that. That's fine, I accept that.

55:18.880 --> 55:22.202
But I feel like your intern or your nanny.

55:23.080 --> 55:25.003
- Look, Maggie. For Christ's sakes...
- And you don't even...

55:25.080 --> 55:29.290
You set all this up, all right?
You gave us all a job. And I'm doing my job.

55:29.360 --> 55:31.010
My job is to write the book.
That's what I'm doing.

55:31.080 --> 55:32.411
- I know that's what you're doing.
- Yes!

55:32.480 --> 55:37.168
So you can't get mad when we all
just play our parts to perfection.

55:37.240 --> 55:39.561
Do you even like me anymore?

55:44.960 --> 55:48.009
What are you trying to get me to say, huh?

55:48.080 --> 55:51.527
It sounds like
I should be asking you that question.

55:55.600 --> 55:58.729
- You want me to get your bag?
- No. I got it, thanks.

56:17.120 --> 56:19.771
- May I sit?
- Yes.

56:30.160 --> 56:32.731
In December,
I am attending a conference in Canada

56:32.800 --> 56:34.962
on ficto-critical anthropology.

56:39.160 --> 56:42.164
Ficto-critical anthropology
is John's field.

56:42.240 --> 56:43.651
I know.

56:44.960 --> 56:46.166
I'm in.

56:48.480 --> 56:51.245
- Really?
- I have no reason to trust you.

56:52.600 --> 56:57.288
On the other hand,
I have absolutely nothing to lose.

56:57.360 --> 57:00.842
I could easily arrange to have John
give a paper at the conference.

57:02.200 --> 57:03.611
Do you think he would accept?

57:03.960 --> 57:07.123
